        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Product Vision\n",
        "\n",
        "Your team is building a **financial technology product**: a domain-scoped Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system that enables analysts to ask structured questions about publicly traded companies in a specific industry and receive grounded, citation-backed answers drawn from SEC 10-K annual filings.\n",
        "\n",
        "This is not a research exercise. Think of the final deliverable as a prototype you would present to a FinTech startup, an investment analytics team, or a regulatory technology firm. The product must be reproducible, auditable, and domain-coherent.\n",
        "\n",
        "Primary workflow:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Google Colab notebooks\n",
        "- Google Drive storage\n",
        "\n",
        "Optional workflow:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Local machine execution\n",
        "- GitHub version control (optional, not required for AD698)\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-important}\n",
        "GitHub is optional in AD698. Do not block progress if your team is not using GitHub.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "# NAICS Industry Code Selection\n",
        "\n",
        "Your team must select a **specific 4-digit NAICS (North American Industry Classification System) code** to scope your product. All company selection, filing downloads, and analytical questions must be anchored to this single industry.\n",
        "\n",
        "Use the official NAICS reference document to browse industry categories and choose one that is analytically interesting and has at least 8-10 publicly traded companies filing 10-Ks:\n",
        "\n",
        "> [NAICS Industry Code Reference (PDF)](https://www.uscourts.gov/file/78724/download)\n",
        "\n",
        "Your NAICS code selection must be documented at the top of your first notebook and justified in 2-3 sentences: why is this industry relevant to financial analysis or FinTech applications?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Examples of analytically rich NAICS 4-digit codes:**\n",
        "\n",
        "| NAICS Code | Industry |\n",
        "|---:|---|\n",
        "| 5221 | Depository Credit Intermediation (Banking) |\n",
        "| 5241 | Insurance Carriers |\n",
        "| 5179 | Other Telecommunications |\n",
        "| 3674 | Semiconductor and Related Device Manufacturing |\n",
        "| 5112 | Software Publishers |\n",
        "| 5242 | Agencies, Brokerages, and Other Insurance Related |\n",
        "| 3559 | Special Industry Machinery Manufacturing |\n",
        "| 4911 | Electric Power Generation, Transmission and Distribution |\n",
        "\n",
        "# Complete Product Pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "Your FinTech product is built in four sequential steps across Modules 1-5. Each step produces artifacts that feed the next.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Step 1 — Industry Scoping, Metadata, and Filing Acquisition (M1)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Select NAICS 4-digit industry and 5-10 public companies\n",
        "- Download 10-K HTML filings from SEC EDGAR for 2015-2025\n",
        "- Parse SEC header metadata and DEI/XBRL fields\n",
        "- Extract all standard 10-K Items into file-level artifacts\n",
        "- **Deliverable:** `filing_metadata.csv`, extracted item files\n",
        "\n",
        "## Step 2 — Item Cleaning and Exploratory Data Analysis (M2)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Select domain-relevant 10-K Items tied to your NAICS industry\n",
        "- Clean raw HTML text: remove boilerplate, table-of-contents noise, artifacts\n",
        "- Conduct EDA: token distributions, company and year coverage, top terms\n",
        "- **Deliverable:** `cleaned_item_metadata.csv`, cleaned item text files\n",
        "\n",
        "## Step 3 — Chunking, Embeddings, and Vector Index (M3)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Chunk cleaned text with token-aware overlap strategy\n",
        "- Generate embeddings via API or open-source model\n",
        "- Build a FAISS vector index with full chunk-level metadata\n",
        "- Validate top-k retrieval quality on test questions\n",
        "- **Deliverable:** `sec10k_chunks.parquet`, vector index artifacts\n",
        "\n",
        "## Step 4 — Grounded Generation, Market Analysis, and Evaluation (M5)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Build a grounded RAG prompt pipeline with citation requirements\n",
        "- Generate answers to industry-relevant financial questions\n",
        "- Fetch historical stock prices for your selected companies using the Yahoo Finance API and conduct a meaningful market-performance analysis tied to your RAG findings\n",
        "- Evaluate retrieval relevance, answer faithfulness, and hallucination risk\n",
        "- Package final report with findings and limitations\n",
        "- **Deliverable:** `rag_answers.csv`, `rag_evaluation.csv`, `yahoo_prices/`, final report\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-note}\n",
        "Module 4 is a mid-project checkpoint. Use that week to catch up, clean up, and confirm Steps 1-3 are complete before starting Step 4.\n",
        ":::\n",
